  "couplingIntensity": "Moderate",
  "created": "2026-03-16",
  "description": "The maqam scale system constrains which MIDI notes the chip will acknowledge — prophecy determines the chip's pitch space. Oracle's active maqam is broadcast as a ModToMod signal that gates Overworld's pitch quantization grid, so only scale-approved notes reach the ERA triangle. Playing a non-maqam note produces silence or a neighboring in-scale snap depending on Overworld's quantization sensitivity. The result: a chip synth that only speaks in modes it has been told to know. Change oracle_maqam to shift the entire chip vocabulary at once. The prophet does not play the chip; the prophet tells the chip what it is allowed to say.",
